{{Infobox football biography | name = Jugurtha Meftah | image = | caption = | fullname = Jugurtha Meftah | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1990|7|28|mf=yes}} | birth_place = [[Tizi Ouzou]], [[Algeria]] | height = | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | currentclub = [[JS Kabylie]] | clubnumber = TBA | youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2011 | youthclubs1 = [[JS Kabylie]] | years1 = 2011– | clubs1 = [[JS Kabylie]] | caps1 = 2 | goals1 = 0 | club-update = 00:00, 9 July 2011 (UTC) }} '''Jugurtha Meftah''' (born July 28, 1990 in [[Tizi Ouzou]]) is an [[Algeria]]n [[Association football|football]] player. He currently plays for [[JS Kabylie]] in the [[Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1]].
==Personal== Meftah was born on July 28, 1990 in [[Tizi Ouzou]]. He comes from a long family of footballers, with three of his cousins having already played for [[JS Kabylie]]: [[Mahieddine Meftah]], [[Mohamed Rabie Meftah]] and [[Rahim Meftah]].<ref>[http://www.lebuteur.com/ligue-1/actualites/jsk-usma-khellili-jai-rencontre-hannachi-et-il-ma-promis-de-maider-pour-ma-lettre-de-liberation La JSK devrait faire confiance aux frères Meftah] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110307055220/http://www.lebuteur.com/ligue-1/actualites/jsk-usma-khellili-jai-rencontre-hannachi-et-il-ma-promis-de-maider-pour-ma-lettre-de-liberation |date=2011-03-07 }}</ref> Two of them, Mahieddine and Rabie, also played for the [[Algeria national football team|Algerian National Team]]. Another cousin, [[Chaâbane Meftah]], is also a footballer and currently plays for JS Kabylie as well.
==Club career== On May 24, 2011, Meftah made his professional debut for [[JS Kabylie]] in a [[2010–11 Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1|league match]] against [[ASO Chlef]] as a 49th-minute substitute for [[Ibrahim Amada]].<ref>[http://www.dzfoot.com/fiches/fiche2.php?fiche_id=5583 ASO 3-0 JSK]</ref>
