===Craig Colton===
'''Craig Colton''' (born 7 October 1988)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.unrealitytv.co.uk/x-factor/x-factor-2011-craig-colton-celebrates-his-birthday/|title=X Factor 2011: Craig Colton celebrates his birthday!|last=McGarry|first=Lisa|date=7 October 2011|publisher=Unreality TV|accessdate=27 November 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202233326/http://www.unrealitytv.co.uk/x-factor/x-factor-2011-craig-colton-celebrates-his-birthday/|archivedate=2 December 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> is from [[Kirkby]] and formerly worked in a biscuit factory in [[Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Scouse+talent+takes+over%3B+acts+head+Merseyside+for+the+judges%27+houses.-a0268068454|title=Scouse talent takes over; acts head Merseyside for the judges' houses. |date=27 September 2011|author=Tina Miles }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.coventrytelegraph.net/passtheremote/2011/10/the-ultimate-guide-to-the-2011.html|title=Ultimate Guide To 2011 X Factor Finalists|date=3 October 2011|author=Marion McMullen|work=[[Coventry Telegraph]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111005121023/http://blogs.coventrytelegraph.net/passtheremote/2011/10/the-ultimate-guide-to-the-2011.html |archivedate=5 October 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/s103/the-x-factor/news/a346361/x-factor-craig-colton-ive-never-hidden-my-sexuality.html|title=X Factor' Craig Colton: 'I've never hidden my sexuality|last=Fletcher|first=Alex|date=19 October 2011|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=19 October 2011|location=London|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111020022000/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/s103/the-x-factor/news/a346361/x-factor-craig-colton-ive-never-hidden-my-sexuality.html|archivedate=20 October 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He was voted out of the competition in week 7, after being in the final showdown with Amelia Lily and receiving the fewest votes, after the result went to deadlock. On 16 January 2012, Colton revealed he is working on his debut album. When asked about the album, he stated "it's very [[Indie music|indie]] and it's very [[Acoustic music|acoustic]] and it's got a nice little hint of [[Jazz music|jazz]]."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.unrealitytv.co.uk/x-factor/x-factor-craig-colton-teases-new-indie-album/|title=X Factor: Craig Colton teases new 'indie' album|accessdate=20 July 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120713155911/http://www.unrealitytv.co.uk/x-factor/x-factor-craig-colton-teases-new-indie-album/|archivedate=13 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Colton unveiled his debut single "Beautiful Surprise" on 12 February, and will go to Los Angeles in the summer to write and record new material with [[Robbie Williams]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.unrealitytv.co.uk/x-factor/x-factors-craig-colton-is-working-with-robbie-williams/|title=X Factor's Craig is working with Robbie Williams!|accessdate=20 July 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029200642/http://www.unrealitytv.co.uk/x-factor/x-factors-craig-colton-is-working-with-robbie-williams/|archivedate=29 October 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Despite identifying as being gay, on 9 October 2012 he revealed to [[NOW (UK magazine)|NOW]] that he was actually [[Bisexual]].<ref>{{cite news|title=My you’ve changed: Thin former X Factor star Craig Colton sheds the pounds and reveals he now likes WOMEN|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2215042/Craig-Colton-sheds-pounds-reveals-likes-WOMEN.html|accessdate=9 October 2012|location=London|work=Daily Mail|first=Kimberley|last=Dadds|date=9 October 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130420063938/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2215042/Craig-Colton-sheds-pounds-reveals-likes-WOMEN.html|archivedate=20 April 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
