===James Michael=== '''James Michael''' (born '''James Michael Stillings'''; 2 February 1991 [[Liverpool]], Merseyside)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/liverpool-news/x-factors-james-michael-celebrates-21st-3352264|title=X-Factor’s James Michael celebrates his 21st with Rebecca Ferguson|last=Collinson|first=Dawn|date=9 February 2012|work=[[Liverpool Echo]]|publisher=[[Trinity Mirror]]|accessdate=28 November 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150111104230/http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/liverpool-news/x-factors-james-michael-celebrates-21st-3352264|archivedate=11 January 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> is from [[Widnes]], Cheshire.<ref name="thefreelibrary1">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Scouse+talent+takes+over%3B+acts+head+Merseyside+for+the+judges%27+houses.-a0268068454 |title=Scouse talent takes over; acts head Merseyside for the judges' houses. – Free Online Library |publisher=Thefreelibrary.com |accessdate=11 November 2011}}</ref> The unemployed singer taught himself a few songs on guitar while job-hunting after finishing school at 16. He describes himself as "not academic" but realised he had a love for music and went to college to study music technology.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metro.co.uk/tv/877340-the-x-factor-2011-final-16-finalists-revealed-for-live-shows|title=The X Factor 2011 final 16: Finalists revealed for live shows|date=2 October 2011|author=Sonia Elks|work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111104055315/http://www.metro.co.uk/tv/877340-the-x-factor-2011-final-16-finalists-revealed-for-live-shows|archivedate=4 November 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He sang "[[Ticket to Ride]]" and was the first in the boys' category to be eliminated from the live shows on 9 October by decision of mentor Gary Barlow, as there was no public vote in the inaugural live show. After Frankie Cocozza was expelled from the show, the public voted for one act from the initial four eliminated from the first live show to replace him, but Michael lost out to Amelia Lily.<ref name="restoreact">{{cite web|url=http://xfactor.itv.com/2011/news/story/read_votes-open-now_item_100199.htm|title=Voting is now open – The X Factor – Story|accessdate=11 November 2011|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111112061932/http://xfactor.itv.com/2011/news/story/read_votes-open-now_item_100199.htm|archivedate=12 November 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The ''[[Liverpool Echo]]'' reported in early 2012 that Michael was recording material for an album.{{Citation needed|date=November 2012}} Since leaving ''The X Factor'', Michael has been taking an interest in modelling and has done many photoshoots since.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heatworld.com/XFactor/2011/11/X-Factors-James-Michael-is-a-model|title=X Factor’s James Michael is a model!|accessdate=22 January 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219140244/http://www.heatworld.com/XFactor/2011/11/X-Factors-James-Michael-is-a-model/|archivedate=19 February 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
