" | "[[Killing Me Softly with His Song]]" - [[Roberta Flack]] | Musical heroes |- | "[[Out Here on My Own]]" - [[Irene Cara]] | Sing-Off | Safe (Majority vote) |- style="background:pink;" ! rowspan="2"| Semi-final | "[[Dancing in the Street]]" - [[Martha and the Vandellas]] | Motown | rowspan="2"| Eliminated (Fourth place) |- style="background:pink;" | "[[Fuckin' Perfect|Perfect]]" - [[Pink (singer)|Pink]] | Song to get you to the final |}
===Janet Devlin=== {{Main article|Janet Devlin}} [[File:Janet Devlin.jpg|thumb|right|206px|Janet Devlin]] '''Janet Devlin''' (born 12 November 1994)<ref name="Belfast Birthday Girl">{{cite web|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/film-tv/news/birthday-girl-janet-devlin-back-on-form-after-a-tough-week-16076842.html |title=Birthday girl Janet Devlin back on form |work=The Belfast Telegraph |date= 14 November 2011|accessdate=15 November 2011}}</ref> is from [[Gortin]], [[County Tyrone]].<ref name="Belfast Birthday Girl" /> Devlin had very little singing experience before ''The X Factor'', only singing in her school, pubs and local talent shows.{{Citation needed|date=November 2011}} She previously uploaded singing videos to [https://www.youtube.com/janetdevlin her official channel] on YouTube on a regular basis,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/user/janetdevlin |title=Janet Devlin's YouTube Channel |accessdate=17 December 2011 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111218223716/https://www.youtube.com/user/janetdevlin |archivedate=18 December 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> where she has now received well over 10 million total views worldwide. Devlin performed "[[Your Song]]" by [[Elton John]] during the audition stage of the competition.<ref name="Mail Janet frontrunner">{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2028411/X-Factor-2011-auditions-Janet-Devlin-secret-YouTube-sensation.html |title=Teen singer Janet is X Factor frontrunner in first show despite crippling nerves before taking the stage |work=Daily Mail |date=21 August 2011 |accessdate=4 July 2012 |location=London |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130419231336/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2028411/X-Factor-2011-auditions-Janet-Devlin-secret-YouTube-sensation.html |archivedate=19 April 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> For the first live show Devlin sang "[[Fix You]]", which was enough to convince Rowland that she deserved a place in the next live show. For the next live shows, Devlin sang "[[Can't Help Falling in Love]]", "[[Sweet Child o' Mine]]", "[[Every Breath You Take]]", "[[I Want You Back]]", "[[Somebody to Love (Queen song)|Somebody to Love]]", "[[Kiss Me (Sixpence None the Richer song)|Kiss Me]]". On week 8 she sang "[[MMMBop]]" and "[[Under the Bridge]]", but was in the bottom two against Misha B. Devlin sang [[Chasing Cars]] for survival, but was voted out of the competition by [[Louis Walsh]] and [[Tulisa]]. [[Kelly Rowland]] refused to vote and the majority vote was used. [[Gary Barlow]] said he would have eliminated Devlin as well. However voting statistics revealed that Devlin received more votes than Misha B meaning if the result went to deadlock, Devlin would have been sent through to the semi-final and Misha B would have been eliminated.
It was reported that Devlin had been offered a recording contract by RKA Records, a record company partly owned by ''[[Dragons' Den (UK)|Dragons' Den]]'' star and entrepreneur [[Duncan Bannatyne]], within 35 minutes of being eliminated from the competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.music-news.com/shownews.asp?H=Janet-Devlin-offered-Dragons-Den-record-deal&nItemID=46369 |title=Janet Devlin offered Dragons' Den record deal |publisher=MusicNews.com |date=28 November 2011 |accessdate=29 November 2011}}</ref> At the end of May 2012 Devlin worked with singer-songwriter [[Eliot Kennedy]],<ref name="Eliot Kennedy">{{cite web|last=Midas Maynard|first=Dean|url=http://www.music-news.com/ShowNews.asp?nItemID=52449|title=Janet Devlin teams up with Eliot Kennedy|accessdate=9 June 2012}}</ref> where she wrote and recorded 3 songs ('Crown of Thorns',<ref>[http://janetdevlinoffic.tumblr.com/post/23950476119/crown-of-thorns My imaginarium | Crown of thorns] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019143138/http://janetdevlinoffic.tumblr.com/post/23950476119/crown-of-thorns |date=19 October 2013 }}</ref> 'Thinking Back Yesterday'<ref>[http://janetdevlinoffic.tumblr.com/post/24011325376/thinking-back-yesterday My imaginarium | Thinking back yesterday] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019144858/http://janetdevlinoffic.tumblr.com/post/24011325376/thinking-back-yesterday |date=19 October 2013 }}</ref> and 'Who Am I Today?'<ref>[http://janetdevlinoffic.tumblr.com/post/24129733105/who-am-i-today My imaginarium | Who Am I Today?] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019145443/http://janetdevlinoffic.tumblr.com/post/24129733105/who-am-i-today |date=19 October 2013 }}</ref>{{citation needed|date=November 2012}}). Her songwriting has also been developed by [[Helen Boulding]].<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/helen-boulding/how-i-survived-juggling-music-and-motherhood_b_1618846.html Helen Boulding: How I Survived Juggling Music and Motherhood<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130823211646/http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/helen-boulding/how-i-survived-juggling-music-and-motherhood_b_1618846.html |date=23 August 2013 }}, ''Huffington Post'' Blog, 26 June 2012.</ref> Devlin has been writing most of her new music along with other songs being co-written for inclusion on an album. The album may feature her song "Crown of Thorns" which she has performed at recent gigs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XQiIqMbbd7s|title=janet devlin - crown of thorns preview|first=|last=Charlotte Grace|date=8 July 2012|publisher=|via=YouTube|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170216182223/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XQiIqMbbd7s|archivedate=16 February 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Devlin used the website PledgeMusic to fund the album, only releasing it if sufficient pre-orders were received.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pledgemusic.com/projects/janetdevlin|title=Janet Devlin: Debut Album|website=PledgeMusic|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130701083444/http://www.pledgemusic.com/projects/janetdevlin|archivedate=1 July 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In December 2012 it was stated that the album would be released in early 2013, having reached 45% of the pledge target within the first two weeks.<ref name="Dean">Dean, Jonathan (2012) "The Great Escapee", ''[[Sunday Times]] Culture'' magazine, 16 December 2012, pp. 24–25</ref>
Devlin performed at Croke Park, in front of a capacity 82,300 crowd, as part of the half-time show for the All Ireland Gaelic Football final on 23 September 2012.<ref name="Dean" /> She performed a cover of "Fix You" and one of her self-penned original songs "Walk Away".<ref name="Dean" /><ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web|url=http://www.ulsterherald.com/2012/09/19/janet-set-for-half-time-croker-gig/ |accessdate=19 September 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120920064953/http://www.ulsterherald.com/2012/09/19/janet-set-for-half-time-croker-gig/ |archivedate=20 September 2012 }}</ref> She performed at the X Factor NSPCC Childline Ball on 18 October, again singing her original song 'Walk Away' and 'Fix You' by Coldplay, helping to raise over half a million pounds for the charity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/the-x-factor/112130-x-factor-2012-childline-ball-raises-over-500000-for-charity.html|title=X Factor 2012 ChildLine ball raises over £500,000 for charity! - The X Factor 2017 - TellyMix|date=19 October 2012|publisher=|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130525021335/http://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/the-x-factor/112130-x-factor-2012-childline-ball-raises-over-500000-for-charity.html|archivedate=25 May 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 3 November 2012 she performed at Casement Park, as part of the pre-match entertainment, for the Michaela Foundation's charity Gaelic Football match in memory of Michaela McAreavey.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/northern-ireland/20187816|title=Stage set for 'Match for Michaela' at Casement Park|date=2 November 2012|publisher=|via=www.bbc.co.uk|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203101009/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/northern-ireland/20187816|archivedate=3 February 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Janet performed for his Holiness, the Dalai Lama on 18 April as part of Irish charity, Children in Crossfire's 'Culture of Compassion' event in Derry.<ref>[http://strabanechronicle.com/2013/04/janet-relishes-dalai-lama-gig/ "Janet relishes Dalai Lama gig"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130414111707/http://strabanechronicle.com/2013/04/janet-relishes-dalai-lama-gig/ |date=14 April 2013 }}, ''Strabane Chronicle'', 8 April 2013. Retrieved 15 June 2013.</ref>
