===Sophie Habibis===
'''Sophie Maria Habibis''', (born 3 November 1991) from [[Tufnel Park]], London. She is the youngest of four children to a father of [[Greek people|Greek]] descent. Prior to the show she was a barmaid in [[Archway, London|Archway]] who had sung karaoke.<ref>{{cite web |title = Sophie Habibis Biography, Picture Gallery & Video |publisher = heatworld.com |url = http://www.heatworld.com/Celeb-AZ/Sophie-Habibis/ |accessdate = 13 November 2013 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131113105847/http://www.heatworld.com/Celeb-AZ/Sophie-Habibis/ |archivedate = 13 November 2013 |df = dmy-all }}</ref> At judges' houses, she performed "[[21 (Adele album)#Track listing|He Won't Go]]" by [[Adele]], and made it through to the Live Shows. In the live shows, Habibis performed [[Katy Perry]]'s "[[Teenage Dream (Katy Perry song)|Teenage Dream]]" in week one, convincing Rowland to keep her in the competition. In following weeks she performed "[[Wherever You Will Go]]", "[[Livin' on a Prayer]]" and "[[Bang Bang (My Baby Shot Me Down)]]". In week four, Habibis was in the bottom two and had to perform in the final showdown against Misha B, she sang "[[Shelter (Birdy song)|Shelter]]" for survival. The judges voted 3–0 to eliminate her including her mentor Kelly Rowland voting against her, claiming Misha wanted to it more. Fellow judge Gary Barlow announced afterwards that he would also have eliminated Habibis.<ref name="metro1"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://xfactor.itv.com/2011/finalists/sophie-habibis |title=The X Factor – Sophie Habibis |publisher=Xfactor.itv.com |accessdate=11 November 2011 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111115230306/http://xfactor.itv.com/2011/finalists/sophie-habibis |archivedate=15 November 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> At the end of the series it was revealed that Habibis had received more votes than Misha B meaning if the result went to deadlock, Habibis would have been saved. She has recently stated plans to release a song in November 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/sophiehabibis/status/255647024022708224|title=“@danjh1988: @sophiehabibis when are you relising a song? x” 12th of November love!! Xx|first=sophie|last=habibis|date=9 October 2012|publisher=|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113094607/https://twitter.com/sophiehabibis/status/255647024022708224|archivedate=13 November 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
