===Jonjo Kerr===
'''Jon-Joseph "Jonjo" Kerr''' in [[Chorley]], Lancashire{{Citation needed|date=October 2011}}; 34, is an infantry soldier in the [[Yorkshire Regiment]], from [[Coventry]] (originally from [[Chorley]], Lancashire). He was deployed to [[Afghanistan]] as part of his duties.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://xfactor.itv.com/2011/finalists/jonjo-kerr |title=The X Factor – Jonjo Kerr |publisher=Xfactor.itv.com |accessdate=11 November 2011 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111107023136/http://xfactor.itv.com/2011/finalists/jonjo-kerr |archivedate=7 November 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He sang "[[You Really Got Me]]" and was the first of the overs category to be eliminated from the live shows on 9 October by decision of mentor Louis Walsh, as there was no public vote in the inaugural live show. The public voted over 10–12 November for one act from the initial four eliminated from the first live show, including Kerr, to replace the expelled Frankie Cocozza, but Kerr lost out to Amelia Lily.<ref name="restoreact" />
Kerr made an appearance on [[choral music|choral]] group [[Military Wives]]' debut studio album, ''[[In My Dreams (Military Wives album)|In My Dreams]]''. Credited to his full name, Jon-Joseph Kerr, the singer appeared on the album's title track, "In My Dreams".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/in-my-dreams/id502289845 |title=Military Wives – 'In My Dreams' – Digital Download |publisher=[[iTunes]] (UK) |date=5 March 2012 |accessdate=6 March 2012 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318150346/http://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/in-my-dreams/id502289845 |archivedate=18 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
Jonjo signed with [[Duncan Bannatyne]]'s Bannatyne Music record label in early 2013 where he is set to release his debut single 'You Are My World'.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tellymix.co.uk/x-factor-2011/136226-video-check-out-a-preview-of-jonjo-kerrs-debut-single.html|title=VIDEO: Check out a preview of Jonjo Kerr's debut single! - X Factor 2011 - TellyMix|date=13 March 2013|publisher=|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130525043628/http://tellymix.co.uk/x-factor-2011/136226-video-check-out-a-preview-of-jonjo-kerrs-debut-single.html|archivedate=25 May 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
