;" ! rowspan="2"| Final (Part 1) | "[[You Got the Love|You've Got the Love]]" - [[Florence and the Machine]] | No theme | rowspan="2"| Safe (1st) |- style="background:lightgreen;" | "[[If I Ain't Got You]]"/ "[[Empire State of Mind]]" - (with [[Tulisa]]) | Mentor duet |- style="background:lightgreen;" ! rowspan="3"| Final (Part 2) | "[[Don't Let Go (Love)]]" - [[En Vogue]] | Song of the series | rowspan="3"| Winner |- style="background:lightgreen;" | "[[Silent Night]]" - [[Celine Dion]] | Christmas songs |- style="background:lightgreen;" | "[[Cannonball (Damien Rice song)|Cannonball]]" | Winners single |}
===Nu Vibe===
'''Nu Vibe''' were a five-piece boy band made up of Jordan Higo (16, from [[Huddersfield]]), Stefan Romer (19, from [[Hampshire]]), Bradley Johnson (16, from [[Rainford]]<ref name="thefreelibrary1"/>), Richard Milford (16, from [[Birmingham]]) and Ashford Campbell (19, from [[Huddersfield]]).<ref name="metro1"/> The band's members successfully auditioned as soloists, but they were knocked out of the competition at the bootcamp stage. The judges then called them back and put them together as a group. They were put through to the live shows by their mentor Tulisa. For the first live show they sang [[Chris Brown (American entertainer)|Chris Brown]]'s "[[Beautiful People (Chris Brown song)|Beautiful People]]". Tulisa then sent them through to the first public vote after the first live show. For the second live show Nu Vibe sang [[U2]]'s "[[With or Without You]]". After the first public vote, Nu Vibe were in the bottom two and had to perform in the final showdown against Frankie Cocozza. Nu Vibe performed "[[Promise This]]" by [[Cheryl Cole]] and were then eliminated from the competition with only their mentor, Tulisa voting in their favour.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://xfactor.itv.com/2011/finalists/nu-vibe |title=The X Factor – Nu Vibe |publisher=Xfactor.itv.com |accessdate=11 November 2011 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111103031941/http://xfactor.itv.com/2011/finalists/nu-vibe |archivedate=3 November 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> On 28 October, it was announced{{where|date=December 2013}} that Ashford Campbell would join The Risk after Ashley Baptiste decided to leave the group. The group had since disbanded in September 2013.
{| class="wikitable collapsible collapsed" style="width:100%; margin:1em auto 1em auto; text-align:center;" |- ! colspan="4" style="background:#BFBFBF;"| ''The X Factor'' performances and results |- ! style="text-align:centre;"| Show ! style="text-align:centre;"| Song choice ! style="text-align:centre;"| Theme ! style="text-align:centre;"| Result |- ! Audition | {{n/a}} | rowspan="4" {{n/a}} | {{n/a}} |- ! Bootcamp (Part 1) | {{n/a}} | {{n/a}} |- ! Bootcamp (Part 2) | "[[Grenade (song)|Grenade]]" - [[Bruno Mars]] | Through to judges' houses |- ! Judges' houses | "[[Written in the Stars (Tinie Tempah song)|Written in the Stars]]"/ "[[Nobody's Perfect (Jessie J song)|Nobody's Perfect]]" - [[Tinie Tempah]] feat. [[Eric Turner (singer)|Eric Turner]]/ [[Jessie J]] | Through to live shows |- ! Live show 1 | "[[Beautiful People (Chris Brown song)|Beautiful People]]" - [[Chris Brown]] feat. [[Benny Benassi]] | Britain vs. America | Saved |- style="background:lightblue;" ! rowspan="2"| Live show 2 | "[[With or Without You]]" - [[U2]] | Love and heartbreak | Bottom two (12th) |- style="background:pink;" | "[[Promise This]]" - [[Cheryl (entertainer)|Cheryl]] | Sing-Off | Eliminated (Twelfth place) |}
===The Risk===
'''The Risk''' was a four-piece boyband that were initially composed of Ashley Baptiste (22, from London), car salesman Andy Merry (20, from [[Ayr]]), [[Burger King]] chef Derry Mensah (21, from London), Marlon McKenzie (28, from [[Manchester]]), and Mitchell McPike. Charlie Healy (25, from [[Coventry]]) was brought into the band, while Marlon and Mitchell were removed from the group at judges houses stage of the competition in a unique decision that has never been made before in X Factor history.<ref name="metro1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://xfactor.itv.com/2011/finalists/the-risk|title=The X Factor – The Risk|publisher=itv.com|accessdate=11 November 2011|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111112143356/http://xfactor.itv.com/2011/finalists/the-risk|archivedate=12 November 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Healy originally auditioned in another group, The Keys, while the other three auditioned as soloists. Andy previously auditioned for ''The X Factor'' in [[The X Factor (UK series 5)|2008]], and came second in the [[United Kingdom in the Junior Eurovision Song Contest 2004|United Kingdom selection]] for the [[Junior Eurovision Song Contest 2004|Junior Eurovision Song Contest]] in 2004. The band came under criticism from a Scottish band from [[Prestwick]], who have been performing together for several years as The Risk. They asked ''The X Factor'' management to change the name of its contestants to avoid confusion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.stv.tv/tv/273910-scots-band-the-risk-want-x-factor-group-to-change-name/|title=STV: Scots band The Risk want X Factor group to change name|publisher=Entertainment.stv.tv|date=9 October 2011|accessdate=11 November 2011|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120613021509/http://entertainment.stv.tv/tv/273910-scots-band-the-risk-want-x-factor-group-to-change-name/|archivedate=13 June 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
On 28 October 2011, just before week four's live show, it was announced that original member Ashley Baptiste had decided to leave the band after stating that his heart did not lie within a boyband any more. He was replaced by Ashford Campbell, as a fourth member. Campbell had been previously a member of Nu Vibe, but his original band had been eliminated on 16 October in week two of the competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/celebs/news/2011/10/30/x-factor-2011-the-risk-s-ashley-baptiste-quit-show-for-jesus-as-uneasy-with-halloween-theme-115875-23524531/ |title=X Factor 2011: The Risk's Ashley Baptiste quit show for Jesus as uneasy with Halloween theme |work=Daily Mirror |date=30 October 2011 |accessdate=12 May 2011 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111030135343/http://www.mirror.co.uk/celebs/news/2011/10/30/x-factor-2011-the-risk-s-ashley-baptiste-quit-show-for-jesus-as-uneasy-with-halloween-theme-115875-23524531/ |archivedate=30 October 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> In week 5, they received the fewest public votes and were sent home, after finding themselves in the bottom three with Johnny Robinson and Kitty Brucknell. Their elimination was a shock to the public as they were the favorites to win The X Factor.
Later on, Ashley went on to release his debut single, "Show the People (How to Love)"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lsjI6J1O5fU|title=Show The People How To Love – Ashley John-Baptiste @AJBOfficial|publisher=YouTube|date=23 January 2012|accessdate=23 January 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140612053855/http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lsjI6J1O5fU|archivedate=12 June 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
In January 2013, they released their debut single: "Missiles", which charted at number 60 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref>{{cite web|title=RISK|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/_/risk/|accessdate=18 September 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921145657/http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/_/risk|archivedate=21 September 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Their second single "Peaches & Cream" is due for release on 4 March 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/peaches-cream-single/id692710915|title=Peaches & Cream - Single by The Risk on Apple Music|website=iTunes|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140415180021/https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/peaches-cream-single/id692710915|archivedate=15 April 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
On 19 September 2014, the group announced that they were splitting up to pursue solo careers.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Risk on Twitter: "We're sad to announce that after 3 amazing yrs, we're going our separate ways. We would like 2 thank u 4 ur support❤️ http://t.co/3O8KssZlML"|url=https://twitter.com/TheRiskOffic/status/513093608975921152|date=19 September 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202173231/https://twitter.com/TheRiskOffic/status/513093608975921152|archivedate=2 February 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
